#inline#mFMb_DS_SetIdleTimer( seconds ; { idleMode } )/*	What it does:	It sets the number of seconds that the myFMbutler DoScript plug-in wil wait before going into the next idle processing for the given idle mode.		Required parameters:	none. It sets the timer for semiSafeIdle when no parameter is passed to the function.		Optional parameters:		idleMode		"safeIlde", "semiSafeIdle" of "unSafeIdle"		returns:		nothing if the syntax is correct			evaluation error 14 (out of range) if the seconds are < 0			evaluation error 1224 (the function is not defined / calculation undefined )			if the idleMode string is incorrect		notes:		the smaller this number, the more frequent the DoScript plug-in will evaluate the trigger.			It *could* slow you down...*/